            <illusdesc>
                <illustration type="plate" location="E">
                    <illusobjdesc>A wreath made of two arched branches forms an oval frame that encloses the central image of three figures, including a man, woman, and child. They may be a family. The man stands in a small wooden boat on the left of the group and faces right. His right leg is raised to stand on the bow of the boat, and his left leg extends backwards out of frame. He bends forward and extends both arms forward with palms. He may reach for the woman. He wears a tunic and has short, curly hair. To his right, a woman with long curly hair and wearing a blue belted gown stands on the bank or shore of a river facing left and looking at the man. She raises both arms at 135 degrees with hands raised and palms out. Her right leg is extended forward and her left leg is bent at the knee. Behind the woman, a female (?) child with curly hair and wearing a tunic stands with her visible right arm raised at 135 degrees. The tunic may be belted. She faces left and looks up toward the male figure. The figures unite on the shore of a river or lake. A rope and a portion of an anchor suggest that the boat is anchored to the shore. An otherwise clear sky is framed by dark clouds on the left side of the frame and rays of light descending from the right side of the frame. Two trees, possibly willow trees, rise on the shore behind the woman. Its branches arch to the left and overlap with the dark clouds.</illusobjdesc>
